author: @psychxx7146
text: This is my opinion :  Bard, just like ChatGPT is yet another test platform to train the model and make it perform better over time, essentially adding on to pre training and RLHF.   While ChatGPT has been designed from the start to be versatile and universal, I view bard as a test platform that will be helpful to infuse LLMs into Google‚Äôs search engine, enhancing the user experience and preventing Microsoft and OpenAI from competing as much as they are doing right now.  TLDR ; Bard will most likely be specialised in web search and ChatGPT will stay the versatile tool it is today

author: @GregoryCarnegie
text: I can't explain it properly but it feels like bard understands patterns in language which ChatGPT understands the language itself.  For example, if I ask bard to port a python function to rust, it will import libraries that don't exist in rust but do exist in python.  If I do the same thing in ChatGPT it will usually recognize that certain libraries in python don't have counterparts in rust.

author: @scottbaker5938
text: After watching this video, I took one of my SQL projects that I have presented in Google Slides and submitted it to Bard for help with the visualizations.  It makes suggestions, but the suggestions are generic (unrelated to my data).  It also suggests changes to graphs that aren't in my presentation at all.  Specifically, it wants me to clean up my line graphs and pie charts, when I have neither in the presentation.  When it tries to summarize the findings, it is able to correct identify which condition in the A/B test produced greater sales, but that was it.  All of the other numbers it suggested were nowhere to be found in my presentation (hallucinations).  I submitted feedback to Google at every step and I hope these tools continue to improve.
